Build 8 with ICU 72: **502/502 targets, 0 failures**.

Artifacts:
- `lib/libJavaScriptCore.a` — 2.3 MB static library
- `bin/jsc` — 19.7 MB ELF64 LSB PowerPC REPL binary

JSC execution verified on POWER8 S824:
```
$ jsc -e 'print(2+2)' → 4
$ jsc -e 'print("Hello from JSC on POWER8 ppc64le")' → Hello ...
$ jsc -e 'fib(20)' → 6765
```

Full ES6+ semantics verified:
- Classes, destructuring, rest spread
- Generators (`function*`, `yield`)
- Map, Set, Symbol.iterator
- Template literals, Promise.resolve
- for...of over generator over linked list

### Codex prediction vs reality
Codex audit flagged `MachineContext.h:192-204,311-324,471-483` as "real source-level
PPC64LE gap" needing ~100 LOC mcontext case. **We didn't hit it.** The #error sites
are inside `ENABLE_JIT`/`ENABLE_DFG_JIT`/`ENABLE_FTL_JIT` guarded regions, which are
compiled out in CLOOP mode. CLOOP doesn't use signal-based preemption so
mcontext_t inspection is unreachable.

This is a GOOD surprise — the CLOOP path is genuinely architecture-agnostic, and
the WebKit WTF ppc64le scaffolding (PageBlock 64KiB, PlatformCPU.h, etc.) was
sufficient.

### Final patch set (4 patches, all upstream-landable)
- `001-ArithProfile-friend-LLIntOffsetsExtractor.patch` — clang-18 qualified friend
- `002-cloop-rb-jsCast-to-uncheckedDowncast.patch` — removed-API fix
- `003-heap-cpp-SetForScope-include.patch` — missing include hygiene
- `004-DeferredWorkTimer-SetForScope-include.patch` — same class as 003

**None are ppc64le-specific.** All help any clang-18 + libc++ JSCOnly CLOOP build.

### Binary properties (jsc on POWER8)
```
ELF 64-bit LSB shared object, 64-bit PowerPC (LE), dynamically linked
deps: libicu*.so.72 (our build), libc++.so.1, libatomic.so.1, libunwind.so.1
```

